  | format =
  | doi =
  | accessdate =  }}</ref> 

The Philadelphia Office of the [[District Attorney]], Daniel Faulkner's family, the [[Fraternal Order of Police]], and numerous other law-enforcement-related organizations have expressed approval of the conviction and [[sentence (law)|sentence]] - being of a view that he murdered Daniel Faulkner while the latter was making a lawful arrest in the line of police duty, and that the former had received a fair trial. Maureen Faulkner, the wife of the deceased, has been a notably vehement advocate for the cause of upholding the verdict and original sentence.<ref>{{cite web
  | last =Cavanaugh
  | first =Andrea
  | authorlink =
