</ref>

== Foreign honours controversy ==
=== House Resolution 407 ===
On May 19, 2006, [[Mike Fitzpatrick|Michael Fitzpatrick]] ([[United States Republican Party|R]]-[[Pennsylvania|PA]]) introduced a [[concurrent resolution]] designated [[United States House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] Resolution 407<ref>{{cite web
  | last =
  | first =
  | authorlink =
  | coauthors =
  | title =HR 407, [[109th US Congress]]
  | work =
  | publisher =GovTrack.us
  | date =
  | url =http://www.govtrack.us/congress/bill.xpd?bill=hc109-407
  | format =
  | doi =
  | accessdate =  }}
</ref>, and on [[June 15]], [[2006]], [[Rick Santorum|Richard Santorum]] ([[United States Republican Party|R]]-[[Pennsylvania|PA]]) introduced the identical [[United States Senate|Senate]] Resolution 102<ref>{{cite web
  | last =
  | first =
  | authorlink =
  | coauthors =
  | title =SR 102, 109th US Congress 
  | work =
  | publisher =GovTrack.us
  | date =
  | url =http://www.govtrack.us/congress/bill.xpd?bill=sc109-102
  | format =
  | doi =
  | accessdate =  }}
</ref>, being that [[US Congress|Congress]]:
* condemn the murder of Philadelphia Police Officer Danny Faulkner
* urge the city of [[Saint-Denis]] to change the name of Rue Mumia Abu-Jamal, and, if they do not, urge the [[Government of France|French government]] to take action against the [[city]] to change the name
* commend police officers all over the world for their commitment to [[public service]] and [[public safety]].

On December 6, 2006, the House of Representatives voted 368-31 in favor of HR407, "Condemning the decision of St. Denis, [[France]], to name a street in honor of Mumia Abu-Jamal, the convicted murderer of Philadelphia Police Officer Danny Faulkner."<ref>{{cite web
  | last =
  | first =
  | authorlink =
  | coauthors =
  | title =Vote results for Roll Call 527
  | work =
  | publisher =US House of Representatives
  | date =December 6, 2006
  | url =http://clerk.house.gov/evs/2006/roll527.xml 
  | format =
  | doi =
  | accessdate =  }}
</ref>

=== Lawsuits involving French municipalities ===
On December 11, 2006, the executive committee of the Republican Party for the 59th Ward of the City of Philadelphia (covering approximately [[Germantown, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|Germantown]], [[Philadelphia]]) [[lawsuit|filed suit]] with two [[http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plainte plaintes]] (criminal complaints on behalf of victims) in forums of the [[French legal system]] against [[Paris#Administration|the government of the city of Paris]] and the city of [[Saint-Denis]] citing the wrong of those cities' actions "glorifying" Mumia Abu-Jamal.<ref>{{cite press release
  | title =59th Republican Ward Executive Committee Files Criminal Charges Against Cities of Paris and Suburb for 'Glorifying' Infamous Philadelphia Cop-Killer
  | publisher =59th Republican Ward Executive Committee - City of Philadelphia
  | date =December 11, 2006
  | url =http://www.politicspa.com/pressreleasedetailed.asp?id=7501
  | accessdate =  }}</ref>

== "Free Mumia" campaign ==
[[Image:MumiaSpanish.jpg|200px|right|thumbnail|[[Barcelona]] street [[propaganda]] calling for the release of Mumia Abu-Jamal]]
{{main|Free Mumia campaign}} 
A broad international movement has allied in support of his cause with noteworthy opposition coalesced about the family of Daniel Faulkner, the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, and the Fraternal Order of Police.

